{"author":{"id":"f9fa446e8ed3e658d3c614258df652e4a274cbe959879543932e114fa617de10"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1771610353,"nonce":"BC0BwF2hu3jh9Inr0qWAP2RDJpU=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDODBZtRc7qn5I_","github-url":"https://github.com/dandi/dandi-cli/issues/1462#issuecomment-3936326207"},"message":"\u003e Resolved. `ZarrAsset.iter_upload()` in `dandi/files/zarr.py` performs differential upload: it compares local entries to remote entries, identifies which files are new or changed, and uploads only those. It also handles deletion of remote entries no longer present locally. This is partial/incremental zarr upload.\n\nHi @yarikoptic, I don't think this issue is resolved.  The overall goal with this feature is to be able to modify the metadata file(s) within a Zarr archive that is stored on DANDI, without having the entire Zarr archive (with imaging chunks) stored locally.  So a user would create a 'skeleton' Zarr archive with only the metadata file(s) locally, modify those metadata files, and then upload the new metadata files.  Thank you.","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1771610353,"nonce":"BwKi8pu4mx4rPvBSuuteUXJYezA=","metadata":{"github-id":"REE_lADODBZtRc6QEgT6zwAAAAVYRW1L"},"status":1}]}